<%- include('../partials/head', { title: 'How It Works' }) %>
<%- include('../partials/nav') %>
<%- include('../partials/disclaimer') %>
<main id="main" class="container narrow">
  <%- include('../partials/flash') %>
  <p class="eyebrow">Simulation engine</p>
  <h1>How USF Capital Works</h1>
  <p class="lead">A guided investor journey wrapped around a backend simulation engine: account creation, demo KYC, virtual funding, allocation, ticking performance, withdrawals and security controls.</p>

  <ol class="steps">
    <li>
      <h2>1. Create your account</h2>
      <p>Register with your email and a password. It takes less than a minute, and no payment details are ever asked for.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h2>2. Verify your identity with a demo check</h2>
      <p>We ask for your name, date of birth, country, and an ID number. This demonstrates a real Know Your Customer flow without sending anything to an outside verification service.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h2>3. Deposit a virtual amount</h2>
      <p>Choose a mock payment method and instantly credit up to $<%= totalCapDollars.toFixed(0) %> in simulated funds. No card, bank, wallet or blockchain transaction is actually used.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h2>4. Allocate across four simulated pools</h2>
      <p>Split your deposit across global equity growth, global macro and FX, fixed income and digital assets. Each allocation opens a simulated position that starts tracking performance right away.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h2>5. Watch it tick for <%= lockYears %> simulated years</h2>
      <p>The backend engine advances portfolio values over time. Local runs use a timer loop, while serverless deploys catch up when requests come in.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h2>6. Withdraw early or wait for maturity</h2>
      <p>Each position locks for <%= lockYears %> simulated years. Early withdrawal applies a declining penalty; matured positions can be withdrawn penalty-free.</p>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <div class="callout">
    <p>This is the important part: the app behaves like a money platform while staying safely fictional. The trading language, prices, balances and returns are all generated by software.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="cta-band card">
    <h2>See it in action</h2>
    <a href="/register" class="btn btn-primary btn-large">Open a Free Simulated Account</a>
  </div>
</main>
<%- include('../partials/footer') %>
